eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 5 Years
Maximum age: 99 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.
Pregnant women and/or nursing patients will be excluded from the study
Patients with Burkitt's or precursor B-lymphoblastic lymphoma

groups.description: Patients receive azacitidine PO daily on days 1-15 and pembrolizumab IV over 30 minutes on day 1. Courses repeat every 3 weeks for up to 24 months or 35 doses, whichever is later, in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity. Patients with disease progression after stopping treatment may receive pembrolizumab for one additional year.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material
Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Treatment (azacitidine, pembrolizumab)

groups.description: Patients receive cisplatin IV over 1 hour and gemcitabine hydrochloride IV over 30 minutes on days 1 and 8, and sirolimus PO daily or three times weekly. Treatment repeats every 3 weeks for up to 8 courses in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Treatment (cisplatin, gemcitabine hydrochloride, sirolimus)

groups.description: Patients undergo proton re-irradiation daily for 3-8 weeks. Beginning 4-12 weeks after completion of radiation therapy, patients then receive pembrolizumab IV on day 1. Treatment repeats every 21 days for up to 8 courses in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.
